{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-novel-version-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon; Novel Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-03",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/themaltesefalconnovel_2603_librivox/maltesefalcon_03_hammett_128kb.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "Three Women",
  "reader_name": "NLizer",
  "page_num": 4,
  "page_total": 4,
  "page_start_sec": 726.144,
  "page_end_sec": 872.16,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.658,
  "corrected": "claude",
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 726.144,
      "end": 726.92,
      "text": "Spade stood still,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 727.0,
      "end": 727.74,
      "text": "shaking his head."
    },
    {
      "start": 728.4,
      "end": 729.8,
      "text": "\"I don't want to show in it.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 730.72,
      "end": 732.38,
      "text": "Freed nodded and went out of the alcove.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 733.28,
      "end": 733.72,
      "text": "In the lobby"
    },
    {
      "start": 733.8,
      "end": 735.74,
      "text": "he halted suddenly and came back to Spade."
    },
    {
      "start": 736.8,
      "end": 739.1,
      "text": "\"Harriman was the house-detective on duty last night,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 739.14,
      "end": 739.5,
      "text": "he said."
    },
    {
      "start": 740.38,
      "end": 741.6,
      "text": "\"He's sure to have seen Archer."
    },
    {
      "start": 742.26,
      "end": 743.92,
      "text": "Shall I caution him not to mention it?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 744.928,
      "end": 747.12,
      "text": "Spade looked at Freed from the corners of his eyes.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 747.98,
      "end": 748.32,
      "text": "\"Better not."
    },
    {
      "start": 748.88,
      "end": 750.56,
      "text": "That won't make any difference as long as"
    },
    {
      "start": 750.56,
      "end": 752.56,
      "text": "there's no connection shown with this Wonderly."
    },
    {
      "start": 753.76,
      "end": 754.6,
      "text": "Harriman's all right,"
    },
    {
      "start": 754.66,
      "end": 755.88,
      "text": "but he likes to talk,"
    },
    {
      "start": 756.56,
      "end": 760.02,
      "text": "and I'd as lief not have him think there's anything to be kept quiet.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 761.184,
      "end": 762.46,
      "text": "Freed nodded again and went away.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 762.976,
      "end": 763.68,
      "text": "Fifteen minutes later"
    },
    {
      "start": 763.72,
      "end": 764.16,
      "text": "he returned."
    },
    {
      "start": 765.26,
      "end": 766.48,
      "text": "\"She arrived last Tuesday,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 766.6,
      "end": 767.96,
      "text": "registering from New York."
    },
    {
      "start": 768.58,
      "end": 769.46,
      "text": "She hadn't a trunk,"
    },
    {
      "start": 769.58,
      "end": 770.34,
      "text": "only some bags."
    },
    {
      "start": 770.92,
      "end": 773.38,
      "text": "There were no phone-calls charged to her room,"
    },
    {
      "start": 773.52,
      "end": 775.56,
      "text": "and she doesn't seem to have received much,"
    },
    {
      "start": 775.6,
      "end": 776.0,
      "text": "if any,"
    },
    {
      "start": 776.1,
      "end": 776.38,
      "text": "mail."
    },
    {
      "start": 777.34,
      "end": 779.46,
      "text": "The only one anybody remembers having seen her"
    },
    {
      "start": 779.46,
      "end": 782.32,
      "text": "with was a tall dark man of thirty-six or so."
    },
    {
      "start": 783.28,
      "end": 785.36,
      "text": "She went out at half-past nine this morning,"
    },
    {
      "start": 785.9,
      "end": 786.92,
      "text": "came back an hour later,"
    },
    {
      "start": 787.14,
      "end": 787.86,
      "text": "paid her bill,"
    },
    {
      "start": 788.04,
      "end": 790.08,
      "text": "and had her bags carried out to a car."
    },
    {
      "start": 791.14,
      "end": 793.48,
      "text": "The boy who carried them says it was a Nash touring car,"
    },
    {
      "start": 793.64,
      "end": 794.68,
      "text": "probably a hired one."
    },
    {
      "start": 795.46,
      "end": 796.62,
      "text": "She left a forwarding address—"
    },
    {
      "start": 796.9,
      "end": 797.72,
      "text": "the Ambassador,"
    },
    {
      "start": 797.96,
      "end": 798.54,
      "text": "Los Angeles.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 799.872,
      "end": 800.38,
      "text": "Spade said,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 800.56,
      "end": 801.38,
      "text": "\"Thanks a lot,"
    },
    {
      "start": 801.38,
      "end": 801.72,
      "text": "Freed,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 802.06,
      "end": 802.74,
      "text": "and left the St."
    },
    {
      "start": 802.84,
      "end": 803.08,
      "text": "Mark."
    },
    {
      "start": 804.22,
      "end": 805.5,
      "text": "When Spade returned to his office",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 805.64,
      "end": 808.34,
      "text": "Effie Perine stopped typing a letter to tell him:"
    },
    {
      "start": 808.62,
      "end": 810.24,
      "text": "\"Your friend Dundy was in."
    },
    {
      "start": 810.4,
      "end": 812.4,
      "text": "He wanted to look at your guns.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 813.48,
      "end": 813.74,
      "text": "\"And?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 815.08,
      "end": 816.8,
      "text": "\"I told him to come back when you were here.\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 817.82,
      "end": 818.22,
      "text": "\"Good girl.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 818.6,
      "end": 819.58,
      "text": "If he comes back again"
    },
    {
      "start": 819.76,
      "end": 820.68,
      "text": "let him look at them.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 821.74,
      "end": 823.12,
      "text": "\"And Miss Wonderly called up.\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 823.84,
      "end": 824.52,
      "text": "\"It's about time.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 824.78,
      "end": 825.94,
      "text": "What did she say?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 827.18,
      "end": 828.08,
      "text": "\"She wants to see you.\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 828.65,
      "end": 831.24,
      "text": "The girl picked up a slip of paper from her",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 831.24,
      "end": 833.66,
      "text": "desk and read the memorandum penciled on it:"
    },
    {
      "start": 834.4,
      "end": 836.62,
      "text": "\"She's at the Coronet, on California Street,"
    },
    {
      "start": 837.248,
      "end": 838.52,
      "text": "apartment one thousand and one."
    },
    {
      "start": 838.68,
      "end": 841.04,
      "text": "You're to ask for Miss Leblanc.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 842.464,
      "end": 842.96,
      "text": "Spade said,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 843.52,
      "end": 843.84,
      "text": "\"Give me,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 844.38,
      "end": 845.32,
      "text": "and held out his hand."
    },
    {
      "start": 846.22,
      "end": 847.67,
      "text": "When she had given him the memorandum",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 847.84,
      "end": 848.8,
      "text": "he took out his lighter,"
    },
    {
      "start": 849.792,
      "end": 850.7,
      "text": "snapped on the flame,"
    },
    {
      "start": 851.23,
      "end": 852.8,
      "text": "set it to the slip of paper,"
    },
    {
      "start": 853.42,
      "end": 856.5,
      "text": "held the paper until all but one corner was curling black ash,"
    },
    {
      "start": 857.38,
      "end": 861.2,
      "text": "dropped it on the linoleum floor, and mashed it under his shoesole."
    },
    {
      "start": 861.74,
      "end": 864.26,
      "text": "The girl watched him with disapproving eyes.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 865.06,
      "end": 865.9,
      "text": "He grinned at her,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 866.08,
      "end": 866.46,
      "text": "said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 867.48,
      "end": 868.44,
      "text": "\"That's just the way it is,"
    },
    {
      "start": 868.48,
      "end": 868.66,
      "text": "dear,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 869.12,
      "end": 869.8,
      "text": "and went out again."
    },
    {
      "start": 871.104,
      "end": 872.16,
      "text": "End of chapter three."
    }
  ]
}